title: Coachella 2025 Weekend 2 Lineup and Schedule: All the Set Times You Need to Know
description: Ed Sheeran returns as a last-minute addition, joining Lady Gaga, Green Day, Charli XCX, Kraftwerk, and more
author: Nina Corcoran

The complete schedule has been revealed for the 2025 Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival, the second weekend of which restarts in Indio, California, on Friday, April 18. Scroll down to check out the full stage and set time breakdown.

Coachella will be headlined, again, by Lady Gaga, Green Day, Post Malone, and Travis Scott. As with the first weekend of the festival, Ed Sheeran has once again been added to the lineup for this second go-around. Sheeran will hit the Mojave Stage on Saturday, April 19, at 3:00 p.m. Pacific Daylight Time. He’s joining the likes of Charli XCX, Kraftwerk, Missy Elliott, Megan Thee Stallion, Tyla, Japanese Breakfast, Arca, and many more. Weezer will not be returning to perform for weekend two attendees. FKA twigs was also set to play both Friday dates, but was forced to cancel her performances due to ongoing visa issues.
